ames throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Oger De Cabulian was born about 1135. He had at least 3 sons."},"et":{"about 1135–":"umbes 1135–Surnud","1155–1180":"1155–1180","1162–Male":"1162–Surnud","1180–1205":"1180–1205","1135–Male":"1135–Surnud","1205":"1205","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","about 1135":"umbes 1135","1162":"1162","1180":"1180"},"fi":{"about 1135–":"noin 1135–Kuollut","1155–1180":"1155–1180","1162–Male":"1162–Kuollut","1180–1205":"1180–1205","1135–Male":"1135–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","about 1135":"noin 1135","1162":"1162","1180":"1180"},"fr":{"about 1135–":"environ 1135–Décédé","1155–1180":"1155–1180","1162–Male":"1162–Décédé","1180–1205":"1180–1205","1135–Male":"1135–Décédé","1205":"1205","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","about 1135":"environ 1135","1162":"1162","1180":"1180","lifeSummary":"Oger De Cabulian est né environ 1135. Il a eu au moins 3 fils."},"de":{"about 1135–":"um 1135–Verstorben","1155–1180":"1155–1180","1162–Male":"1162–Verstorben","1180–1205":"1180–1205","1135–Male":"1135–Verstorben","1205":"1205","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","about 1135":"um 1135","1162":"1162","1180":"1180","lifeSummary":"Oger De Cabulian wurde um 1135 geboren. Er hatte mindestens 3 Söhne."},"ht":{"about 1135–":"about 1135–Desede","1155–1180":"1155–1180","1162–Male":"1162–Desede","1180–1205":"1180–1205","1135–Male":"1135–Desede","1205":"1205","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","about 1135":"about 1135","1162":"1162","1180":"1180"},"hu":{"about 1135–":"1135 körül–elhunyt","1155–1180":